  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting school principals as leaders in the curriculum reform in Lithuania</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ministry of Education, Science and Sport officials, policy makers, teachers, parents, local municipalities, education practitioners, school leaders.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will create a two-stage training programme to support first 30 and then 300 principals across
the country in becoming instructional leaders and lead the curriculum reform. In addition, the Ministry will be supported in reviewing strategic issues related to school leadership.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This is a two-year European Union funded project, started on June 15th 2020 and its objective is to support school principals in Lithuania and assist them to implement the changes to the school curriculum as planned by the Ministry of Education, Science and Sport. The expected long-term impact of the project is to contribute towards strengthening the quality of school
leadership and specifically the quality of instructional leadership in schools in Lithuania.</narrative>
  </description>
